HEBREW PIPELINE:
- Fixed Hebrew subtag tokenization: slash (/) now correctly appends to the preceding
  token (ה/ not /ה), giving proper morphological segmentation in hebrew_subtags.db
- Rewrote hebrewEncode.js with clean source/target DB separation:
    Reads hebrew_processed.db (read-only source)
    Writes fresh hebrew_encoded.db with _encoded table names (not _processed)
    PRAGMA journal_mode=DELETE prevents WAL/SHM sidecar files from persisting
- Fixed DB naming typo: hebrw_subtags → hebrew_subtags throughout
- WAL/SHM cleanup now runs on every DB that is opened, source and target both,
  in finally blocks so cleanup happens even on error

GREEK PIPELINE:
- Created greekEncode.js: dynamically introspects _processed table schemas,
  converts Beta-code to Greek Unicode, writes _encoded tables to greek_encoded.db
- Created GreekSubtags.js: whitespace-only tokenizer (no slash handling),
  reads greek_encoded.db, writes greek_subtags.db
- greekProcess.js was already in place for Greek column cleaning and tag extraction

PIPELINE ARCHITECTURE RESTRUCTURE:
- Replaced flat master script with a language stack model:
    HebrewStack.js: hebrewProcess → hebrewStats → hebrewEncode → HebrewSubtags → compiledStats
    GreekStack.js:  greekProcess → greekStats → greekEncode → GreekSubtags → compiledStats
    00.master.js simplified to: import → HebrewStack → GreekStack
- Each stack script spawns sub-scripts sequentially via child_process.spawn
- compiledStats.js runs at the end of each stack and is tolerant of missing source DBs
  (gracefully compiles whatever stats are available, skips if neither is present)

STATISTICS:
- Created hebrewStats.js → hebrewStat.db (table: hebrewStats)
- Created greekStats.js → GreekStat.db (table: greekStats)
- Created compiledStats.js → CompiledStats.db (table: combinedStats):
    Aggregates both stat DBs additively by Book key
    TotalRows = Math.max across languages (verse counts overlap, not additive)
    RowsWithAnyTag and all tag columns are summed across languages
    CORPUS_TOTAL row always sorted to the top

